This paper deals with cross-lingual word embeddings, which are commonly used in natural language processing (NLP) tasks such as machine translation, sentiment analysis, and named entity recognition. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), which deals with NLP and related topics. 

The paper also proposes a self-learning algorithm that iteratively improves the cross-lingual mappings, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). 

The authors use adversarial training and unsupervised initialization techniques, which are common in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and information retrieval (cs.IR) research. 

Finally, the paper evaluates its method on standard datasets, which often involve image and text processing tasks, falling under the category of computer vision (cs.CV).
